subsection.text:
Radio Marti and Television Marti, which constitute the Office of Cuba Broadcasting, shall continue programming and content production consistent with the mission and activities as described in the Radio Broadcasting to Cuba Act (
                Public Law 98–111
              ) and the Television Broadcasting to Cuba Act (
                Public Law 101–246
              ), and continue existing within the Voice of America of the United States International Communications Agency, established in section 101.

